<paragraph blockId="51.[673,1212,1135,1700]" pageId="51" pageNumber="58">
Two further sheets at BM under this name have labels in the hand of Baker.The first, BM000801015, formed part of the Sir H. &amp; Lady Barkly Herbarium. The label reads “ 
<taxonomicName box="[852,926,1674,1699]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Dryopteridaceae" genus="Lastrea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" pageId="51" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
