<figureCitation box="[494,571,311,338]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="54.[288,299,967,983]" captionTargetBox="[226,1097,214,937]" captionTargetId="figure-318@54.[226,1097,215,936]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIG. 29. — Distribution of Dryopteris wardii (Baker) Kuntze in the Seychelles islands group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5197391" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5197391/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="60">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). Little is known about the ecology of the species, except that one of the collections was made at 
<emphasis box="[522,539,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="60">c.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[544,613,374,401]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="53" pageNumber="60" unit="m" value="550.0">
<elevation box="[544,613,374,401]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="53" pageNumber="60" unit="m" value="550.0">550 m</elevation>
</quantity>
on 
<collectingCountry box="[112,178,406,433]" name="India" pageId="53" pageNumber="60">Mahé</collectingCountry>
. No recent collections of the species appear to have been made
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
